Dan Fleder, Head of VRP, Head of Stone Ridge Partnership Services
Dan Fleder is the Head of Variance Risk Premium (VRP) and the Head of Stone Ridge Partnership Services at Stone Ridge Asset Management.  Prior to Stone Ridge, Dan was the Chief of Staff for Operations at KCG and previously was the Head of Risk Management at GETCO.  Dan started his career at McKinsey & Company after receiving his PhD in Operations Research, Master's in Statistics, and Bachelor's in Engineering from the University of Pennsylvania's Wharton School and Engineering School.


Paul Germain, Head of Alternative Lending
Paul Germain is the Head of Alternative Lending at Stone Ridge Asset Management.  Prior to joining Stone Ridge, Paul was the Global Head of Prime Services at Credit Suisse.  Paul was previously a Partner at Goldman Sachs and Co-Head of the US Client Franchise in Prime Brokerage.  Paul earned an MBA from Harvard Business School and BSE in Management from University of Pennsylvania (Wharton).


Erick Goralski, Head of Client Strategies
Erick Goralski is the Head of Client Strategies and a co-founder of Stone Ridge Asset Management.  Prior to Stone Ridge, Erick was the Head of Deutsche Bank’s US Structured Products business focused on the wealth management industry.  Erick was previously at Lehman Brothers on the US Equity Structured Products desk.  Erick holds a BS in Economics from Miami University.


Yan Gu, Head of Quantitative Research, Head of China
Yan Gu is the Head of Quantitative Research and Head of China at Stone Ridge Asset Management.  Prior to joining Stone Ridge, Gu was the Head of Quantitative Equities Research at Magnetar Capital.  Previously, Gu worked in quantitative research at Citadel and Lehman Brothers. Gu holds a PhD in Theoretical Physics from University of Pennsylvania and a Masters in Finance and Investment from Stanford University.


Robert Gutmann, Head of Product Development & Execution
Robert Gutmann is the Head of Product Development and Execution and a co-founder of Stone Ridge Asset Management.  Prior to Stone Ridge, Robert was the Head of Delta-One Synthetic Solutions at RBC Capital Markets.  He started his career at Morgan Stanley, where he became a senior trader in the Delta-One Structured Products group.  Robert received his BA in Mathematics and Music from Columbia University.


Patrick Kelly, COO
Patrick Kelly is the Chief Operating Officer and a co-founder of Stone Ridge Asset Management.  Prior to Stone Ridge, Patrick worked at Magnetar Capital, most recently as the Chief Operating Officer of Quantitative Strategies.  Prior to Magnetar, Patrick had roles in risk, portfolio valuation, and trading at Citadel and DE Shaw.  Patrick holds a BS in Finance from DePaul University and is a CFA charter holder.


Jim Rothwell, Head of Legal
Jim Rothwell is the Head of Legal at Stone Ridge Asset Management.  Prior to joining Stone Ridge, Jim was a partner in the Securities and Equity Derivatives Group at Davis Polk & Wardwell LLP.  Jim holds a JD from Harvard Law School and a BS in Biochemistry and Molecular Biology from Harvard University. 


Tomer Seifan, Head of Structured Investments
Tomer Seifan is the Head of Structured Investments at Stone Ridge Asset Management.  Prior to joining Stone Ridge, Tomer was the Head of Structuring and Solutions for Global Markets in the Americas at BNP Paribas.  Previously, Tomer led a variety of structuring and structured product groups at both BNP Paribas and Bank of America.  Tomer started his career in the Financial Institutions Group at Davis Polk & Wardwell after receiving his JD from Georgetown University and his BA from Yale University.


Ross Stevens, CEO
Ross Stevens is the CEO and Founder of Stone Ridge Asset Management.  Prior to founding Stone Ridge, Ross was a member of the Investment Committee and Co-Head of the Portfolio Managers Committee at Magnetar Capital.  Previously, Ross was Global Co-Head of Equities at Jefferies and Global Head of Electronic Trading at Bank of America.  Ross started his career in quantitative research at Goldman Sachs Asset Management after receiving his PhD in Finance and Statistics from University of Chicago (Booth) and his BSE in Finance from University of Pennsylvania (Wharton).


Yan Zhao, Head of Reinsurance
Yan Zhao is the Head of Reinsurance at Stone Ridge Asset Management.  Prior to joining Stone Ridge, Yan was a senior management consultant at the Boston Consulting Group.  She started her career at Morgan Stanley, as a trader in the Delta-One Structured Products group.  Yan holds an MBA from Harvard Business School and a BA with honors in Economics from Harvard University.




